Anthony Adoki’s new song, Loke-Loke has won the heart of several fun-seekers as a result of the song’s creative content. Produced by Flo Rocka, the song, The Nation gathered, has generated more buzz among fans and has become a regular anthem on the lips of many music lovers. The River State-born gospel singer grew up in Lagos and started his music professionally in 1996 where he worked with several artists of local and international repute.   Structured music industry will impact Nigeria’s economy,…     Excitement as MCSN holds AGM     Nuno Zigi set for debut EP NDO   Adoki holds a certificate in the music business, from the School of Audio Engineering in Cape Town, South Africa. He won several music awards in his early years and has featured in several annual music concerts like Cityfm, Praise in the city, RCCG, and June 8th Praise Day with his gospel band. Adoki and his gospel group have traveled to several countries for charity concerts with the first studio-recorded album in 2010 and since then, he and his crew have released several singles from the yet-to-be-released second album. His debut album ‘Don’t Give Up’ was launched in 2010 with his hit track ‘Durotimi’ (Stay with me). As observed by music analysts, the song topped the list of songs on Lagos’ Inspirational FM station for several weeks, and on many music charts across the nation.